To investigate the morphological evolution of BWO and the nature of the organics, hydrothermal time-dependent experiments (6 h, 12 h and 18 h) were performed, and the morphology of BWO was characterized by SEM and TEM (Fig. 2
                        ). CQDs/HBWO-6 was assembled by numerous nanosheets, which aggregated tightly together and formed a spherical microstructure (Fig. 2a). When the solvothermal treatment time increased to 12 h and 18 h, the Bi2WO6 microstructures began to transform from a solid spherical structure into a hollow spherical structure (Fig. 2b, c) through an inside-out Ostwald ripening process [31], in which smaller interior crystallites inside dissolved and then transferred to the exterior surface to grow larger crystallites. The as-prepared sample without PVP was composed of irregular nanosheet aggregates (Fig. S1). This suggested that PVP plays an important role in the construction of hollow structures, which is consistent with previous studies [34]. SEM images (Fig. 2c, d) of CQDs/HBWO-18 and HBWO demonstrated a negligible effect of a crystalline or morphological structure after calcination treatment. The TEM image in Fig. 2e clearly showed the synthesized CQDs/HBWO-18 hollow spherical structure, which is consistent with the SEM results. The HRTEM image in Fig. 2f displayed a lattice spacing of 0.273 nm, which corresponded to the (200) planes of orthorhombic Bi2WO6 
                        [22]. Nanoparticles with a diameter of ~ 6 nm were attached to the Bi2WO6. These nanoparticles were confirmed to be graphitic carbon because the lattice spacing was 0.321 nm, which is close to the (002) spacing of graphitic carbon [35]. In the FT-IR spectra of CQDs/HBWO-18 and HBWO (Fig. 1 b), the C–H stretching vibration disappeared after calcination treatment at 450 °C, which is the CQDs decomposition temperature, and the color of the as-prepared sample powder changed from light brown to beige (Fig. S2). Given that previous research has shown that PVP is a new precursor for the preparation of carbon dots, we inferred that these particles might be CQDs that were formed by PVP.
